00:00:59.120 --> 00:01:05.220
skate skiing which can take you from absolute amateur to actual - Olympian - Olympic Champion

00:01:05.220 --> 00:01:05.890
Yeah.

00:01:09.460 --> 00:01:11.040
Ryan, where have you taken us to now?

00:01:11.040 --> 00:01:14.200
Well Doug we just happen to be standing on the edge of a meteorite crater.

00:01:14.200 --> 00:01:15.280
Right here?

00:01:15.280 --> 00:01:16.060
Right here.

00:01:16.060 --> 00:01:22.100
Over two billion years ago, a meteorite almost 15 kilometres across impacted the Earth and

00:01:22.340 --> 00:01:27.819
went almost 15 kilometres down into it, and created a crater that was 250 kilometres wide.

00:01:28.980 --> 00:01:33.520
When the meteorite struck, the shockwaves created what's called shatter cones. And on

00:01:33.530 --> 00:01:37.910
your drive up to Windy Lake Provincial Park you can actually see some of those representations

00:01:37.910 --> 00:01:42.060
at the A.Y. Jackson lookout in the summertime, and in the wintertime, you can stop in at Science North.

00:01:43.060 --> 00:01:45.760
That's incredible. And we're standing on the edge of it?

00:01:45.770 --> 00:01:47.050
We're standing on the edge of it.

00:01:50.390 --> 00:01:53.560
So Doug we've seen a lot of cool things in
the park, but one of the cooler things is

00:01:53.560 --> 00:01:58.880
definitely our winter camping yurts. But what makes it the coolest thing is that you can ski right to it.

00:01:58.979 --> 00:02:03.619
So our yurts have an electric heater, an electric light, it sleeps six people, you have a large

00:02:03.620 --> 00:02:07.620
deck, a BBQ, a fire pit, and a winter heated
privy.

00:02:08.170 --> 00:02:12.160
You have your world-class ski trails out the front door, you have snowshoe trails out the

00:02:12.160 --> 00:02:16.820
back door, the lake down the hill for ice
fishing -- it's just all right there for your taking.

00:02:16.830 --> 00:02:17.990
You've got everything you need right there

00:02:18.020 --> 00:02:20.500
You've got everything there and it'san absolute wonderful place to be.

